{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Change in legislation to encourage & support new mums getting back to work.",
        "additional_details": "Research has shown that working mums set better examples to their children, and hands-on mums shape more emotionally rounded children. But mums are currently forced to choose between giving up work, not seeing their children, or struggling financially. Becoming a mum is being treated as a punishable offence. To the benefit of creating well-rounded children with strong role models and views of working and earning an income, mums must be supported in being the examples our children need us to be.",
        "background": "PROPOSED LEGISLATION:\r\n1. Mandatory for employers to offer part-time return-to-work up to 3y after birth\r\n2. Give mums returning to work an allowance towards childcare OR:\r\n3. Provide 15h/week subsidised nursery from 1-3 years to cover gap between maternity pay ending and full nursery hours starting",
